            ],
            "subtype": "sidebar",
            "sidebar_type": "treasure_and_rewards",
            "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
            "image": {
                "type": "image",
                "name": "Treasure and Rewards",
                "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png"
            },
            "html": "While a giant porcupine is well protected, it's also highly sought after by hunters. Its soft flesh is very tasty when cooked, a delicacy prized in woodland communities. The porcupine's quills are another valued commodity, reaching nearly 3 feet long. Skilled artisans use the smaller quills to craft beautiful, wearable art, while the longer ones can be made into lightweight throwing weapons."
        }
    ],
